&lt;p&gt;Do you consider yourself a strong team player with exceptional communication skills? Do you take pride in your work and have good attention to details. Then this maybe the perfect role you are looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to become part of an established team providing support to users of our electronic health record systems across the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical application support team (CAST)is a small team that provides a service desk to support end users of Carenotes and Adastra. This includes an overnight call rota to manage out of hours calls. The team are part of the electronic health records team in the information management and technology department. We are currently working from home and full support will be provided to facilitate this, our base is at Littlemore Mental Health Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have good listening and customer service skills, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Melanie Trinder Job title Clinical Application Support Team Lead Email address Melanie.trinder@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk Telephone number 07795 401 403&lt;/p&gt;
